  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      Comparison of two operative techniques (on-pump vs off-pump)of coronary revascularisation of
      the best treatment concept for patients older or 75 years old.

      Hypothesis: The coronary bypass operation without use of the heart-lung machine
      (off-pump=OPCAB) reduces the combined endpoint in comparison with the conventional coronary
      bypass operation (on-pump).
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
